cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing the service placement problem for IoT-fog-cloud architecture, which involves networking and communication between different nodes in the network. 
2) cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses distributed processing for IoT and fog computing, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
3) cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves optimization of power consumption for processing and networking, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4) cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimization of information processing and communication in IoT networks. 
5) cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves optimization of computational resources for IoT, which can be considered as a computational engineering problem.
